Re: the Jena figures I quoted earlier, the 50 seconds reported time
(now down at 45 after I shifted set implementations) is for 
3729 tests, where &quot;test&quot; means &quot;invocations of a JUnit testZZZ()
method&quot;. By running outside Eclipse I appear to be able to shave
another 5s off the reported time.

Some of the tests are more multi-facteted than I&#39;d really like, such as:

    public void testRemove()
        { 
        testRemove( &quot;S ?? ??&quot;, &quot;S ?? ??&quot; );
